FBIS4-43878 "drweu121aa_94004" FBIS-WEU-94-121 Daily Report 22 Jun 1994 INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS Spain Offers Logistic Support Spain Offers Logistic Support LD2206154694 Madrid RNE International in Spanish 1300 GMT 22 Jun 94 LD2206154694 Madrid RNE International Spanish BFN [Text] [Announcer] In statements made to this radio station Javier Solana, Spanish foreign minister, said Spain was willing to contribute to the logistics of the French intervention in Rwanda as soon as the UN Security Council has given the go-ahead for this military operation. Javier Solana. [Begin Solana recording] Here is the latest information. This morning -- local time in New York -- the UN Security Council will pass a resolution allowing a multinational force to distribute humanitarian aid along the Rwandan borders to Rwandan citizens who are being expelled. It will not be deployed in Rwanda. Spain's role: Spain will vote in favor of this Security Council resolution. It not only supports this resolution, Spain was the first country to suggest that such an initiative had to be taken. Secondly, what kind of aid are we going to contribute? Spain will not deploy armed forces in the field. We will lend logistical support to the whole operation which will be run by the French. The French already have troops deployed in Africa and they will be in charge of the operation. [end recording] [Announcer] Up until now the French have received support from the members of the Western European Union meeting today in Brussels.
